Before changing anything, inspect the biggest consumers:

console.log($(".k-edit-form-container:visible").height());

$(".k-edit-form-container:visible")
    .children()
    .each(function () {
        console.log(this.className, $(this).outerHeight(true));
    });

For a quick, safe reduction, I'd try CSS like this:

/* Reduce vertical spacing between editor rows */
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-form-container .k-edit-label,
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-form-container .k-edit-field {
    margin-top: 2px !important;
    margin-bottom: 2px !important;
}

/* Reduce form padding */
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-form-container {
    padding: 8px !important;
}

/* Reduce spacing between rows */
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-form-container .k-form-field,
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-form-container .k-form-layout-row {
    margin-bottom: 4px !important;
}

/* Reduce button area padding */
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-edit-buttons {
    padding: 4px 8px !important;
    min-height: auto !important;
}

If you're using Telerik FormLayout inside the popup, an even bigger win is often:

.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-form-layout {
    row-gap: 4px !important;
}

A quick way to identify the real culprit is:

console.log("Buttons:",
    $(".k-edit-buttons:visible").outerHeight(true));

console.log("Form:",
    $(".k-edit-form-container:visible").outerHeight(true));

console.log("Content:",
    $(".k-window-content:visible").outerHeight(true));
